race.comment: GRAMMY'S SUNSHINE (10) was close up off a longish spell resuming over 1000m at Cranbourne. Had come off a Flemington jumpout win and is sure to have taken fitness. The filly wasn't disgraced in Stakes company on debut and can realise her potential this preparation. Draws low and Coffey is a positive jockey engagement replacing the apprentice.  BEGONIA (9) debuts and has jumped out well. Yendall sticks from that and will give the filly every chance from a soft gate. SHE'S LOADED (11) resumes again and both of her starts have been in much tougher metro company. The jumpouts have been encouraging and it won't surprise to see her race well. HARBOUR CITY (1) can build on his narrow defeat at Mt Gambier first-up.
